      induced with a 4% acetic acid enema. Colonic myeloperoxidase activity was used as
      a surrogate marker for neutrophil infiltration. Control rats fed rat chow had
      little colonic myeloperoxidase activity; geometric mean, 0.27 U/g of tissue. Rats
